### Project 1: Linux Command Cheat Sheet
# Repo Name: linux-cli-cheatsheet
# File: README.md

# Linux CLI Cheat Sheet

## 🔧 File Handling
- `ls -l` : List files with details
- `cp source.txt destination.txt` : Copy file
- `mv old.txt new.txt` : Rename or move file
- `rm file.txt` : Delete file
- `touch newfile.txt` : Create empty file

## 📁 Directory Handling
- `mkdir new_folder` : Create directory
- `cd foldername` : Change directory
- `pwd` : Show current path
- `rmdir foldername` : Remove empty directory
- `rm -r foldername` : Remove directory recursively

## 📊 System Monitoring
- `top` : Live system processes
- `htop` : Enhanced process viewer (if installed)
- `df -h` : Disk usage
- `free -h` : Memory usage
- `uptime` : System load and uptime

## 🌐 Networking
- `ping google.com` : Check connectivity
- `ifconfig` / `ip a` : Network interfaces
- `netstat -tulnp` : Listening ports and services
- `curl example.com` : Fetch web page
- `wget http://example.com/file.txt` : Download file

## 🔐 Permissions
- `chmod +x script.sh` : Make script executable
- `chown user:group file.txt` : Change ownership
- `ls -l` : View file permissions

## 📦 Package Management (Debian-based)
- `sudo apt update` : Update package list
- `sudo apt upgrade` : Upgrade packages
- `sudo apt install packagename` : Install package
- `sudo apt remove packagename` : Uninstall package

